      },
      "date": "2017-11-07 17:03:55.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n(2 comments)\n\nI would be ok with this patch landing as-is, if there is a follow-on patch that moves stack_trap() to test-framework.sh and converts other trap calls to use stack_trap() so that future tests developed by copying existing code will use it also.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "62df2e3b48dca2e99ee23bd8606a75bc5020eaf3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 626,
        "name": "Quentin Bouget",
        "email": "quentin.bouget@cea.fr",
        "username": "bougetq"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-08 08:34:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(2 comments)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "80be36a61ea39871293b7fa09c25183e29015cbd",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-11-09 10:13:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> The test harness provides enough isolation between tests so that\n> traps do not outlive their test: each test is run in a subshell\n> of its own, in run_one_logged().\n\nOK.  It might be useful to add a comment to this effect, if this patch needs\nto be refreshed, or in a later patch.\n\n> My \"landing planning\" was:\n>\n>    update one test in sanity-hsm (this patch)\n>    update all tests in sanity-hsm\n>    update all tests in sanity (I would move stack_trap() to test-framework.sh)\n>    update many/all tests (gradually like we do with coding style,\n>      or all at once depending on how much work this represents)\n> \n> Do you think I should make stack_trap() available in test-framework.sh sooner?\n\nIt wouldn't hurt to put it into test-framework.sh from the start.  That way it is available for use in other tests if the patch from step #3 isn't developed or landed right away.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
